data.title: Prince Philippe, Count of Paris Facts for Kids
data.meta_description: Prince Philippe, Count of Paris facts. Prince Philippe of Orléans, Count of Paris (Louis Philippe Albert; 24 August 1838 – 8 September 1894), was disputedly King of the French from 24 to 26 February 1848 as Louis Philippe II, although he was never officially proclaimed as such.
